    <p class="c6"><span class="c7">2. Understanding the Nine Building Blocks:</span></p>
    <ul class="c8 lst-kix_r0f4mw81x6k6-0 start">
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0">
            <span class="c2">
                Customer Segments: Identify target customer groups and their
                specific needs.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0">
            <span class="c2">
                Value Proposition: Define the products or services that address
                customer pain points and deliver value.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0">
            <span class="c2">
                Channels: Outline the channels through which value is delivered
                to
                customers and how they are reached.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0">
            <span class="c2">
                Customer Relationships: Describe the types of relationships
                established with customers to ensure satisfaction and loyalty.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0">
            <span class="c2">
                Revenue Streams: Detail the sources of revenue generated by the
                business model.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0">
            <span class="c2">
                Key Resources: Identify the essential assets, infrastructure,
                and
                capabilities required to deliver the value proposition.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0">
            <span class="c2">
                Key Activities: Enumerate the critical tasks and processes
                necessary
                for executing the business model.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0">
            <span class="c2">
                Key Partnerships: Highlight strategic alliances and
                collaborations
                that enhance the value proposition.
            </span>
        </li>
        <li class="c3 li-bullet-0">
            <span class="c2">
                Cost Structure: Break down the costs incurred in operating the
                business model.
            </span>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="c5"><span class="c4"></span></p>
